			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingResearch">
				<def>StartingResearch</def>
				<project>ColoredLights</project>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingResearch">
				<def>StartingResearch</def>
				<project>GeothermalPower</project>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>HerdMigration</incident>
				<intervalDays>20</intervalDays>
				<repeat>True</repeat>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>RaidFriendly</incident>
				<intervalDays>5</intervalDays>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>0.9</chance>
				<context>PlayerStarter</context>
				<trait>GreatMemory</trait>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>0.95</chance>
				<context>PlayerStarter</context>
				<trait>Industriousness</trait>
				<degree>2</degree>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
				<def>GameStartDialog</def>
				<text>Scientist 1: What just happened?! This isn't the lab!

Scientist 2: No...we've missed the mark..by..a lot?

Scientist 1: Where are we located?

Scientist 4: It seems like we have no service, no GPS; no nothing....just a wasteland...

Scientist 3: I'm freaking out! Excited! And HORRIFIED! 

Scientist 1: Calm down, let's figure out where we're at; and survive. We've all learned how to get this far in the program right?

*They all agree to persevere through this trying time and to create an outpost until help arrives. If it ever does or can...*</text>
				<textKey>GameStartDialog</textKey>
				<closeSound>GameStartSting</closeSound>
			</li>
			</parts>
		</scenario>
	</ScenarioDef>

<ScenarioDef> <!-- The Soldier Lost in Time -->
		<defName>TheSoldierLostinTime</defName>
		<label>The Soldier Lost in Time</label>
		<description>You were fighting hard in the 1st World War of a non-distinct Earth timeline. As you led a flank charge to take hold of an enemy outpost...A BLINDING FLASH OF WHITE HAPPENS! Leaving you and your men blinded until you feel nothing.
Waking up with just you and your gear in this unknown land. But you know you must survive!
- A SciFi Tale of a Soldier-</description>
		<scenario>
		<summary>In the middle of a battle you saw a blinding flash of white; then you were in no man's land. Despite knowing nothing; can you survive?</summary>
		<playerFaction>
			<def>PlayerFaction</def>
			<factionDef>PlayerColony</factionDef>
		</playerFaction>
		<parts>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns">
				<def>ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns</def>
				<pawnChoiceCount>1</pawnChoiceCount>
				<pawnCount>1</pawnCount>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_PlayerPawnsArriveMethod">
				<def>PlayerPawnsArriveMethod</def>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_PawnFilter_Age">
				<def>PawnFilter_Age</def>
				<allowedAgeRange>18~35</allowedAgeRange>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>1</chance>
				<context>PlayerStarter</context>
				<trait>Nerves</trait>
				<degree>2</degree>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>1</chance>
				<trait>Tough</trait>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>0.8</chance>
				<context>NonPlayer</context>
				<trait>Industriousness</trait>
				<degree>1</degree>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ForcedTrait">
				<def>ForcedTrait</def>
				<chance>0.55</chance>
				<context>PlayerStarter</context>
				<trait>Psychopath</trait>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Gun_AssaultRifle</thingDef>
				<quality>Excellent</quality>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Apparel_FlakPants</thingDef>
				<quality>Poor</quality>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Apparel_FlakJacket</thingDef>
				<quality>Poor</quality>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Apparel_AdvancedHelmet</thingDef>
				<stuff>Steel</stuff>
				<quality>Normal</quality>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>MedicineIndustrial</thingDef>
				<count>5</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>MealSurvivalPack</thingDef>
				<count>20</count>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ScatterThingsAnywhere">
				<def>ScatterThingsAnywhere</def>
				<thingDef>WoodLog</thingDef>
				<count>100</count>
				<allowRoofed>True</allowRoofed>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ScatterThingsAnywhere">
				<def>ScatterThingsAnywhere</def>
				<thingDef>Steel</thingDef>
				<count>50</count>
				<allowRoofed>True</allowRoofed>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>SelfTame</incident>
				<intervalDays>1</intervalDays>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>RaidEnemy</incident>
				<intervalDays>10</intervalDays>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>WandererJoin</incident>
				<intervalDays>10</intervalDays>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_CreateIncident">
				<def>CreateIncident</def>
				<incident>TravelerGroup</incident>
				<intervalDays>25</intervalDays>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
				<def>GameStartDialog</def>
				<text>*The blinding flash ends leaving the soldier in a state of adrenaline and panic*

Soldier: AAGH!!! Wait...this isn't the battlefield...where am I?

Soldier: None of this look familiar...is this the future?

Soldier: The future of the world after the war? Was it a loss or victory?! 

*The soldier paces around this new land unsure of what to think*

Soldier: I don't even know if this is the future..or a different world...I don't know anything besides my brothers are probably dying on the battlefield without me!

*After sulking for a few moments the soldier snaps out of it*

Soldier: No point in draggin' myself down. I need to stay sharp and survive until I know more!</text>
			</li>
		</parts>
	</scenario>
	</ScenarioDef>

<ScenarioDef> <!-- It Was Almost Summer -->
		<defName>ItWasAlmostSummer</defName>
		<label>It Was Almost Summer</label>
		<description>The bell rings in Vellerant High, all the students pouring out the halls ready for Summer vacation to begin!
As a group get ready to race out the door A BLINDING FLASH OF WHITE CUTS THEM OFF!
Transported to the future, the past, a new world; somewhere they don't recognize. But all tthey have is each other and this new land they must conquer...or die in.
-A SciFi tragedy of highschool life Tale-</description>
	<scenario>
	<summary>As the bell rings for Summer Vacation to begin; this group of highschoolers won't be seeing free time anytime soon as they're whisked away to a new world!</summary>
		<playerFaction>
			<def>PlayerFaction</def>
			<factionDef>PlayerColony</factionDef>
		</playerFaction>
		<parts>
			<li Class="ScenPart_ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns">
				<def>ConfigPage_ConfigureStartingPawns</def>
				<pawnChoiceCount>5</pawnChoiceCount>
				<pawnCount>5</pawnCount>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_PlayerPawnsArriveMethod">
				<def>PlayerPawnsArriveMethod</def>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
				<def>GameStartDialog</def>
				<text>Student 2: Woah! What just happened?!

Student 4: I don't know man but that wasn't fun...where are we?

Student 1: WHERE ARE WE!? WHEN ARE WE!? THIS LOOKS LIKE AN END OF THE WORLD SCENARIO!

Student 3: Calm down guys, this isn't a video game right? There's always an explaination...

Student 2: Is there though? A white flash of light then BAM! We're not in Kansas anymore? I'm a bit freaked out too!

Student 4: Look guys...I know we're all scared but worst case we're in the wild somewhere..Let's just get our shit together alright? Figure this out and panic later when we can sleep.

*Everyone agrees to pull themselves together for now*</text>
			</li>
			<li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
				<def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
				<thingDef>Apparel_BasicShirt</thingDef>
				<stuff>Hyperweave</stuff>
